03/04/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A sizeable downsizing of the Serbia-Montenegro military is planned by 2010, army deputy chief General Major Zdravko Ponos said in an interview published Sunday (2 April) by the daily Politika. He said the number of army troops must be cut from the current 50,000 to less than 30,000 in 2010. The plans envisage reduction of the military to 36,000 troops by the end of 2007, Ponos added.
In other news, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Serbia-Montenegro sealed an agreement Friday on military co-operation. The document was signed during the first official visit of BiH Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic to Belgrade. (Politika, Tanjug - 02/04/06; Danas - 01/04/06) 
